	<script type="application/ld+json" class="yoast-schema-graph">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":"Article","@id":"https://foragerchef.com/fresh-wild-mushroom-conserve/#article","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://foragerchef.com/fresh-wild-mushroom-conserve/"},"author":{"name":"Alan Bergo","@id":"https://foragerchef.com/#/schema/person/31d81645fe879af0594ccb1cae80f720"},"headline":"Wild Mushroom Conserve (Pickled Mushrooms)","datePublished":"2014-01-28T00:37:20+00:00","dateModified":"2025-09-03T20:51:37+00:00","wordCount":1619,"commentCount":191,"publisher":{"@id":"https://foragerchef.com/#organization"},"image":{"@id":"https://foragerchef.com/fresh-wild-mushroom-conserve/#primaryimage"},"thumbnailUrl":"https://foragerchef.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Chanterelle-Mushroom-Conserve-5-of-5.jpg","articleSection":["Chanterelles","Chicken of the Woods","Hedgehogs","Morels","Mushroom Preserves","Pickles, Preserves, Etc","Wild Mushroom Recipes"],"inLanguage":"en-US","potentialAction":[{"@type":"CommentAction","name":"Comment","target":["https://foragerchef.com/fresh-wild-mushroom-conserve/#respond"]}]},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://foragerchef.com/fresh-wild-mushroom-conserve/","url":"https://foragerchef.com/fresh-wild-mushroom-conserve/","name":"Wild Mushroom Conserve Recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://foragerchef.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://foragerchef.com/fresh-wild-mushroom-conserve/#primaryimage"},"image":{"@id":"https://foragerchef.com/fresh-wild-mushroom-conserve/#primaryimage"},"thumbnailUrl":"https://foragerchef.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Chanterelle-Mushroom-Conserve-5-of-5.jpg","datePublished":"2014-01-28T00:37:20+00:00","dateModified":"2025-09-03T20:51:37+00:00","description":"Chef Alan Bergo shares his recipe for wild mushroom conserve, a great way to preserve your mushroom haul, and probably the best pickled mushroom you will ever taste.","breadcrumb":{"@id":"https://foragerchef.com/fresh-wild-mushroom-conserve/#breadcrumb"},"inLanguage":"en-US","potentialAction":[{"@type":"ReadAction","target":["https://foragerchef.com/fresh-wild-mushroom-conserve/"]}]},{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https://foragerchef.com/fresh-wild-mushroom-conserve/#primaryimage","url":"https://foragerchef.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Chanterelle-Mushroom-Conserve-5-of-5.jpg","contentUrl":"https://foragerchef.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Chanterelle-Mushroom-Conserve-5-of-5.jpg","width":1200,"height":1200,"caption":"Chanterelle Mushroom Conserve"},{"@type":"BreadcrumbList","@id":"https://foragerchef.com/fresh-wild-mushroom-conserve/#breadcrumb","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https://foragerchef.com/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Wild Mushroom Recipes","item":"https://foragerchef.com/category/wild-mushroom-recipes-2/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"name":"Wild Mushroom Conserve (Pickled Mushrooms)"}]},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://foragerchef.com/#website","url":"https://foragerchef.com/","name":"Forager | Chef","description":"Award-winning chef, author and forager Alan Bergo. Food is all around you.","publisher":{"@id":"https://foragerchef.com/#organization"},"potentialAction":[{"@type":"SearchAction","target":{"@type":"EntryPoint","urlTemplate":"https://foragerchef.com/?s={search_term_string}"},"query-input":{"@type":"PropertyValueSpecification","valueRequired":true,"valueName":"search_term_string"}}],"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Organization","@id":"https://foragerchef.com/#organization","name":"Forager Chef","url":"https://foragerchef.com/","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https://foragerchef.com/#/schema/logo/image/","url":"https://foragerchef.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/FORAGER-CHEF®.jpg","contentUrl":"https://foragerchef.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/FORAGER-CHEF®.jpg","width":500,"height":500,"caption":"Forager Chef"},"image":{"@id":"https://foragerchef.com/#/schema/logo/image/"},"sameAs":["https://www.facebook.com/Foragerchef/"]},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://foragerchef.com/#/schema/person/31d81645fe879af0594ccb1cae80f720","name":"Alan Bergo","description":"Chef, Amateur Mycologist.","sameAs":["https://foragerchef.com/about/"]},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Wild Mushroom Conserve","author":{"@id":"https://foragerchef.com/#/schema/person/31d81645fe879af0594ccb1cae80f720"},"description":"Probably the greatest wild mushroom pickle/preserve you will ever taste. \nYield: 1 qt canning jar ","datePublished":"2014-01-27T18:37:20+00:00","image":["https://foragerchef.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Chanterelle-Mushroom-Conserve-1-of-5.jpg","https://foragerchef.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Chanterelle-Mushroom-Conserve-1-of-5-500x500.jpg","https://foragerchef.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Chanterelle-Mushroom-Conserve-1-of-5-500x375.jpg","https://foragerchef.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Chanterelle-Mushroom-Conserve-1-of-5-480x270.jpg"],"recipeYield":["15","15 Servings"],"prepTime":"PT15M","cookTime":"PT20M","totalTime":"PT35M","recipeIngredient":["Scant 2 lbs  small young mushroom buttons.  (28-30 oz will fit a quart jar.  Chanterelle buttons are my favorite here )","3 cloves 7 grams garlic  (thinly sliced )","1/2 cup flavorless oil for sauteeing (grapeseed or canola )","1 teaspoon  5 grams kosher salt (a generous teaspoon )","3/4  cup water","1/2 cup apple cider or white wine vinegar","2 teaspoons fresh chopped thyme (fresh only )","1  dried bay leaf (or use fresh )"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Read through the entire recipe before proceeding.","name":"Read through the entire recipe before proceeding.","url":"https://foragerchef.com/fresh-wild-mushroom-conserve/#wprm-recipe-21677-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Clean your mushrooms by swishing them quickly in cold water while you clean them to ensure they&#39;ll have liquid to give up when they hit the heat. Transfer the mushrooms to a tray lined with a few paper towels and allow them to rest and release some liquid. I like to do this overnight in the fridge to allow them to dry out a bit.","name":"Clean your mushrooms by swishing them quickly in cold water while you clean them to ensure they&#39;ll have liquid to give up when they hit the heat. Transfer the mushrooms to a tray lined with a few paper towels and allow them to rest and release some liquid. I like to do this overnight in the fridge to allow them to dry out a bit.","url":"https://foragerchef.com/fresh-wild-mushroom-conserve/#wprm-recipe-21677-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In a wide pan with high sides, or a soup pot, gently heat the oil and the sliced garlic slowly on medium heat until the garlic begins to turn golden. Take your time here, as the more color you can put on the garlic, the better the finished product will taste. Do not burn the garlic.","name":"In a wide pan with high sides, or a soup pot, gently heat the oil and the sliced garlic slowly on medium heat until the garlic begins to turn golden. Take your time here, as the more color you can put on the garlic, the better the finished product will taste. Do not burn the garlic.","url":"https://foragerchef.com/fresh-wild-mushroom-conserve/#wprm-recipe-21677-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"When the garlic is perfectly golden, add the mushrooms, salt and herbs, stir so the salt can help draw out the mushroom liquid, then cover the pan, cooking on medium heat, and allow the mushrooms to give up their juice and halt the cooking of the garlic. The mushrooms should give off a good amount of water.","name":"When the garlic is perfectly golden, add the mushrooms, salt and herbs, stir so the salt can help draw out the mushroom liquid, then cover the pan, cooking on medium heat, and allow the mushrooms to give up their juice and halt the cooking of the garlic. The mushrooms should give off a good amount of water.","url":"https://foragerchef.com/fresh-wild-mushroom-conserve/#wprm-recipe-21677-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Once the mushrooms have wilted and their liquid has released, add the water and vinegar, then bring the mixture to a rolling boil.","name":"Once the mushrooms have wilted and their liquid has released, add the water and vinegar, then bring the mixture to a rolling boil.","url":"https://foragerchef.com/fresh-wild-mushroom-conserve/#wprm-recipe-21677-step-0-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Finally, put the mushrooms in a quart jar, pack them down, then bring the liquid back to a boil, and pour the boiling liquid over the mushrooms. Wiggle a chopstick around in the jar to get out air pockets, adding extra pickling liquid as needed. From here the mushrooms can be stored in the fridge and will last for months as long as they&#39;re kept under their liquid.","name":"Finally, put the mushrooms in a quart jar, pack them down, then bring the liquid back to a boil, and pour the boiling liquid over the mushrooms. Wiggle a chopstick around in the jar to get out air pockets, adding extra pickling liquid as needed. From here the mushrooms can be stored in the fridge and will last for months as long as they&#39;re kept under their liquid.","url":"https://foragerchef.com/fresh-wild-mushroom-conserve/#wprm-recipe-21677-step-0-5"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"If you want to water bath can the mushrooms, leave 1/2 inch of headspace at the top. Depending on the size of your mushrooms, you may have a little pickle liquid and some mushrooms leftover.","name":"If you want to water bath can the mushrooms, leave 1/2 inch of headspace at the top. Depending on the size of your mushrooms, you may have a little pickle liquid and some mushrooms leftover.","url":"https://foragerchef.com/fresh-wild-mushroom-conserve/#wprm-recipe-21677-step-0-6"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Press the mushrooms down to make sure they are completely covered with liquid--add a little oil to cover if they threaten to pop up, then screw on the lid, then process the jar(s) in a water bath like regular cucumber pickles: 10 minutes for pints, 15 minutes for quarts. Store opened jars in the fridge.","name":"Press the mushrooms down to make sure they are completely covered with liquid--add a little oil to cover if they threaten to pop up, then screw on the lid, then process the jar(s) in a water bath like regular cucumber pickles: 10 minutes for pints, 15 minutes for quarts. Store opened jars in the fridge.","url":"https://foragerchef.com/fresh-wild-mushroom-conserve/#wprm-recipe-21677-step-0-7"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4.84","ratingCount":"87","reviewCount":"4"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Hello!\r\nWhat would you recommend to do with left over liquid, it feels wrong to just trow it out 🙃","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Mari"},"datePublished":"2025-11-20"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I've used this recipe with chanterelles and morels and had great success. I was considering trying this recipe with chopped up lobster mushrooms. Would that work fine? Would you make any adjustments?","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Cameron"},"datePublished":"2025-10-10"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"God to know. Thanks Alan.\r\n\r\nAlso, I was curious how long they would last in jars if you didn’t refrigerate right away, and didn’t do the water can bath (i.e. just pickled them and put them in the jar and covered with liquid)? I was thinking of sending some as gifts, and figured mailing them after cooking would be best to get them there while fresh as possible. Just wanted to see how long you think they could last without refrigeration. Thanks again Alan!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Matt"},"datePublished":"2025-09-05"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Hello Alan,\r\n\r\nWonderful recipe. I’ve used it on chants and hedgehogs. Outta this world. Sorry if it’s already been asked, but I was curious if this recipe works for field/meadow mushrooms?\r\n\r\nThank you so much for sharing this recipe!\r\n\r\nBest,\r\nMatt","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Matt"},"datePublished":"2025-09-03"}],"recipeCategory":["Snack"],"recipeCuisine":["Italian"],"keywords":"Conserve, Mushroom Conserve, Pickled Wild Mushrooms","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","servingSize":"1 oz","calories":"91 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"4 g","proteinContent":"1 g","fatContent":"8 g","saturatedFatContent":"1 g","transFatContent":"0.03 g","sodiumContent":"6 mg","fiberContent":"2 g","sugarContent":"1 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"7 g"},"@id":"https://foragerchef.com/fresh-wild-mushroom-conserve/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://foragerchef.com/fresh-wild-mushroom-conserve/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https://foragerchef.com/fresh-wild-mushroom-conserve/"}]}</script>
